{"article_id":"2NbdXjBM7HzA1SYN","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" Generally , the report shows","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that things are better","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"than we ' d expected","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"and certainly better","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"than we ' d thought a few months ago , \"","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"said Paul Dales , senior United States economist for Capital Economics .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"\" But we ' re still not making enough progress","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"to bring that unemployment rate down significantly and rapidly . \"","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Mitt Romney , the Republican presidential nominee , said in a statement","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that the jobs report was evidence of the need","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to change the nation ' s economic policies .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"\" Today ' s increase in the unemployment rate is a sad reminder","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that the economy is at a virtual standstill , \"","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"He also noted","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"that October ' s unemployment rate of 7.9 percent was higher than the 7.8 percent","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"when Mr. Obama took office in January 2009 .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Unemployment peaked at 10 percent in October of Mr. Obama ' s first year in office ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"and has been skidding downward very , very slowly since then .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Economists were hopeful","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"that","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"once the election was over","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"and Congress addressed the major fiscal tightening","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"scheduled for the end of this year ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"job and output growth could speed up further .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"\" If we can do this kind of job growth with all the uncertainty out there ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"imagine","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"if we were to clear up those tax issues","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"and hold back the majority of tax increases","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"that are pending at the end of the year , \"","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"said John Ryding , chief economist at RDQ Economics .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"\" We could do much better in 2013 ,","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"maybe as well","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"as we appeared to be doing earlier this year . \"","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"The jobs snapshot for October was based on surveys","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"conducted too early in the month","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"to capture work disruptions across the East Coast","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"caused by Hurricane Sandy .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Economists expect","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"that businesses and employment will resume their normal activity by the next jobs survey , in mid-November ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"and that some industries will even show an increase in hiring","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"because of the storm .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"\" We had a lot of lost hours worked","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"and production stuff still delayed ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"but much of that will be offset by hiring of emergency workers , government workers and construction ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to do all that emergency fixing , \"","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"said Diane Swonk , chief economist at Mesirow Financial .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"In October , the biggest job gains were in professional and business services , health care and retail trade ,","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"the Labor Department said .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"Government payrolls dipped slightly .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"State and local governments have been shedding jobs in most months over the last three years .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"One of the low points of the report was in hourly wages ,","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"which remained flat in October","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"after showing barely any growth in the previous several months .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Please verify","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":4},{"id":72,"text":"\" Perhaps the decline in real wages is a factor here","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"in being able to employ more people , \"","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"Mr. Ryding said .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"\" It ' s something","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"to keep in mind","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"when we think about creating jobs","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"and whether we ' re maybe creating the wrong sort of jobs . \"","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"A report from the National Employment Law Project , a liberal research and advocacy organization","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"that focuses on labor issues ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"found","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"while the majority of jobs","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"lost in the downturn","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"were middle-income jobs ,","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"the majority of the jobs","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"created since then","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"had been lower-wage ones .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Stock markets opened higher after the jobs report on Friday ,","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"but fell for the day ,","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"apparently weighed down later by a number of concerns from the possible lingering effects of the storm to the uncertainty about the outcome of the election .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"The United States has now posted job gains for 25 consecutive months ,","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"but the increases have been barely large enough","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"to absorb the increase in the working population .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"About 12 million unemployed people remain waiting for work ,","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"with about two out of five of those people out of a job for more than six months .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"That is in addition to more than eight million people","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"who are working part time","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"but really want full-time jobs .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"\" I ' m not just competing against all the other people","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"who are out of work , \"","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"said Griff Coxey , 57 , of Cascade , Wis. ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"who was laid off in May from his controller job at a small business .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"\" I ' m also competing against all those people","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"who are actually working","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"but are underemployed . \"","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Like two million other idle workers , Mr. Coxey is scheduled to lose his unemployment benefits the last week of the year ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"when the federal extensions expire .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"he still had some savings","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"to fall back on ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"but many workers do not .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Labor advocates and many economists have been urging Congress to renew the benefits as part of their discussions of the \" fiscal cliff \" during their postelection session .","depth":5},{"id":114,"text":"So far , though , the issue has received little attention ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"and analysts worry","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"that ending extended benefits could disrupt whatever forward momentum","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"the economy has .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"\" Federal unemployment benefits are one of the most effective stimuli","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"we have , \"","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"said Christine L. Owens , the executive director of the National Employment Law Project .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"\" The recovery is still fragile , \"","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"she said ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"\" and to pull that amount of income and expenditure out of the economy","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"- particularly at a time","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"when people thinking about the holiday season -","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"will have a significant impact on not just those individuals and their families , but the economy as a whole . \"","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"Friday ' s jobs report was unlikely to affect policy from the Federal Reserve ,","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"which has pledged open-ended stimulus","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"until the job market improves \" substantially . \"","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"\" The Fed desires both a substantial and sustainable improvement in labor market conditions","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"and is likely to read recent payroll growth as a positive step in the right direction , but just one step in a longer journey , \"","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"said Michael Gapen , director of United States research and global asset allocation at Barclays Capital .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":265,"left":186,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":166,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":151,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":140,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":138,"right":139,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":138,"left":137,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":0,"right":136,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":136,"left":134,"right":135,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":145,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":142,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":8,"right":141,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":147,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":14,"right":146,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":165,"left":156,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":19,"right":155,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":20,"right":154,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},